Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper focuses on automated pavement crack detection and measurement using convolutional neural networks, which is a subfield of computer vision. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The proposed method uses an ensemble of convolutional neural networks, which is a machine learning technique. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes an AI-based approach for pavement crack detection and measurement. 
4. cs.RO (Robotics) - The proposed method can be applied in robotics for road inspection and maintenance. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - Although less likely, this paper could also belong to the cs.CR sub-category as pavement crack detection is important for road safety and security.
